A lovely little puzzle game that can be played in two ways: map out your solution before activating the percussive projectiles, so you get the final rhythm first time, or activating the projectiles at the beginning so each solution's audio is evolves as you work it out. The latter is more relaxing and more satisfying sonically, but undermines some of the puzzling because solutions can be discovered easier and sometimes by accident. The game is a good length but rolls the mechanics and more challenging puzzles out a little too steadily for my taste. Still, I enjoyed it a great deal. If you enjoyed this definitely check out a similar title called Micron which has more varied and interesting sounds as well as a less linear structure.
